-- Ecobank announces departure of CEO Tanoh
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 01:01PM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, March 11 (Reuters) - Pan-African lender Ecobank <ETI.LG> announced the departure of its embattled Chief Executive Thierry Tanoh on Tuesday and said deputy group CEO Albert Essien would replace him.

Ecobank also reinstated with immediate effect Finance Director Laurence do Rego, who was dismissed in January following a dispute over her qualifications, a statement released by the bank said.